A/C in most of Rome seemed to be ineffective against extreme heat, so I don't think Hotel Grifo is alone, but temperature in the room was often warmer than on the terrace.	Every day you return to a clean room and if it´s hot outside, you´ll have AC inside.	Not so good things: 1)The temperature in the shower was fluctuating and became cold when you started to feel better after a tiring day (in addition there was no hair-dryer).	Hotel Grifo provided us with 2 fans and they also provide some compensation - the nights cooled down so it was bearable.	After notifying the desk clerk of our hot room we finally asked for a fan which did help some.